b'{"warnings":{"query":{"*":"Formatting of continuation data will be changing soon. To continue using the current formatting, use the \'rawcontinue\' parameter. To begin using the new format, pass an empty string for \'continue\' in the initial query."}},"query":{"pages":{"5328954":{"pageid":5328954,"ns":0,"title":"Coal Tiger","revisions":[{"contentformat":"text/x-wiki","contentmodel":"wikitext","*":"{{Superherobox| <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics-->\\nimage=[[Image:Coaltiger.jpg|250px]]\\n|caption=T\'Chaka the Coal Tiger.\\n|comic_color=background:#ff8080\\n|character_name=Coal Tiger\\n|real_name=T\'Chaka\\n|species=[[Mutant (Marvel Comics)|Human Mutant]]\\n|publisher=[[Marvel Comics]]\\n|debut=\'\'[[A-Next]]\'\' #4 (1999)\\n|creators=[[Tom DeFalco]]<br>[[Brent Anderson]]\\n|alliance_color=background:#ffc0c0\\n|alliances=[[A-Next]]\\n|aliases=\\n|powers=Ability to shapeshift into a feline humanoid<br>Superhuman strength and agility<br>Enhanced senses<br>Retractable razor sharp claws\\n|}}\\n\\n{{Refimprove|date=March 2010}}\\n\'\'\'Coal Tiger\'\'\' (\'\'\'Prince T\'Chaka II\'\'\') is a [[fictional character]] who appeared in the [[Marvel Comics]]\' [[Marvel Comics 2|MC2]] series \'\'[[A-Next]]\'\'. He is the son of T\'Challa, King of Wakanda and the superhero known as [[Black Panther (comics)|Black Panther]].\\n\\n==Fictional character biography==\\nWhen a [[racist]] team of villains called the [[Soldiers of the Serpent]] attacked T\'Challa\'s friend N\'Kano (who was on a diplomatic mission for [[Wakanda (Marvel Comics)|Wakanda]] in New York), A-Next tried to save him. As the Serpents battled with the heroes of A-Next, T\'Challa\'s son T\'Chaka charged into battle. While [[Mainframe (comics)|Mainframe]] tried to convince the youth to leave the battle, T\'Chaka [[shapeshifting|shapeshifted]] into a feral black [[werecat]] called the \\"Coal Tiger\\". Coal Tiger\'s bestial abilities were able to turn the tide in A-Next\'s favor. He was offered membership with the team after the battle was won, but he declined, stating that he would be available to help if they needed him.<ref>\'\'A-Next\'\' Vol. 1 #4</ref>\\n\\nWhen all of the members of A-Next were captured by an evil version of A-Next called the [[Revengers]], Coal Tiger was one of the many heroes who came to free the captured superheroes. When A-Next was freed and the Revengers were defeated, Coal Tiger finally agreed to join the team.<ref>\'\'A-Next\'\' Vol. 1 #4</ref>\\n\\n==Powers and abilities==\\nCoal Tiger can change into a humanoid cat creature. In his feline form, he has superhuman strength and agility, as well as enhanced senses and retractable razor-sharp claws on his fingers and toes.\\n\\n==Other Coal Tigers==\\nCoal Tiger is also the name of an alternate universe version of T\'Challa himself, who appeared in \'\'[[Avengers (comics)|Avengers]]\'\' vol 1 #355 as a member of the Gatherers, a group of former Avengers from different universes.<ref>\'\'Avengers Forever\'\' #1-12</ref>\\n\\nA Coal Tiger is mentioned in \'\'[[Captain America]]\'\' vol 1 #389 as an opponent of the [[Zambia]]n villainess [[Impala (Marvel Comics)|Impala]].<ref>\'\'[[Captain America]]\'\' vol 1 #389</ref>\\n\\nIn \'\'Black Panther\'\' vol 3 #60, the Coal Tigers are mentioned as being a rank in the Panther Cult.<ref>\'\'Black Panther\'\' vol 3 #60</ref>\\n\\nThe name \\"Coal Tiger\\" was one of several that Stan Lee and Jack Kirby were bandying back and forth as a possible name for the character who in mainstream continuity in the [[Marvel Universe]] became Black Panther.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goodcomics.comicbookresources.com/2010/04/16/comic-legends-addendum-before-he-was-black-panther/comment-page-1/ |title=Comic Legends Addendum: Before He Was Black Panther\\u2026 &#124; Comics Should Be Good! @ Comic Book Resources |publisher=Goodcomics.comicbookresources.com |date= |accessdate=2011-01-06}}</ref>\\n\\n==In other Media==\\nWhile the character has never appeared, in [[Ultimate Avengers 2]] the powers of the Coal Tiger seemed to be part of the Panther line. Both King T\'Chaka and T\'Challa transform into cat creatures during their fights with [[Herr Kleiser|Kleiser]].\\n\\n==References==\\n<references />\\n{{MC2}}\\n{{Black Panther}}\\n\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics 2]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics superheroes]]\\n[[Category:Fictional shapeshifters]]\\n[[Category:Fictional werecats]]\\n[[Category:Wakandans]]\\n[[Category:Characters created by Tom DeFalco]]"}]}}}}'